01/02/2005
ATHENS, Greece -- The government on Monday (31 January) announced tough new measures aimed at corrupt judges and officials. 
They include prison sentences of ten years and fines of 100,000 euros.
In other news, Greek police have arrested four Pakistanis, a Syrian and a Romanian for forcibly detaining illegal immigrants and demanding ransom for their release. 
The immigrants, mostly Pakistani nationals, allegedly were asked to pay more than 7,500 euros each. 
(ANA - 01/02/05; AFP, ABC, MPA - 31/01/05)
